Now that jungle diversity has improved, I'd like to call our attention to the next least diverse role: ADC's. Now as you can generally there's a bit of a holy quad of ADC's.

In my honest opinion:
{{champion:104}} 
{{champion:222}} 
{{champion:429}} 
{{champion:15}}
Need nerfs.

{{champion:119}} 
{{champion:67}} 
{{champion:18}} 
{{champion:81}} 
{{champion:22}} 
{{champion:236}} 
Are fine, mostly, little tweaks here and there, but their problem is mostly a case of being outclassed by the quad.

{{champion:96}} 
{{champion:6}} (Fills in a Bruiser role, but his ADC needs buffing)
{{champion:110}} 
{{champion:29}} (Dear god twitch, poor Twitch, a shadow of your former self.)
{{champion:133}} (Fills In a Bruiser role, but her ADC needs buffing)
{{champion:21}} (Yes, I feel she needs some buffs here and there, but less so than the others.)

Need buffs, some more than others.
While I know that some of their kits can be toxic e.g. {{champion:29}} ({{champion:82}} Huehuehue toxic get it?) having them like this is NOT the way to go...

replies.body:
> [{quoted}](name=MasterCorgi,realm=EUW,application-id=3ErqAdtq,discussion-id=eFmm1GXi,comment-id=,timestamp=2015-03-24T20:05:34.091+0000)
>
> Now that jungle diversity has improved, I'd like to call our attention to the next least diverse role: ADC's. Now as you can generally there's a bit of a holy quad of ADC's.
> 
> In my honest opinion:
> {{champion:104}} 
> {{champion:222}} 
> {{champion:429}} 
> {{champion:15}}
> Need nerfs.

{{champion:104}} I think Graves is fine and will be falling out of favor as tanks are becoming popular again.  I don't think he should be nerfed.
{{champion:222}} I think Jinx is very close to balance but could maybe use some little nudges to weaken her laning considering how strong her teamfighting is.  A really slight nerf (increase mana cost by 10 or so at all levels?) on Zap! would probably put her in a good place.
{{champion:429}} I feel like Riot should task a developer with continually experimenting with Kalista's kit until the community can agree that she isn't as frustrating anymore... I feel like the community isn't going to like her even if she is balanced or even underpowered number-wise...
{{champion:15}} I think Sivir is in the same boat as Graves and will likely shift out of the meta fairly soon.  I feel like she has well defined weaknesses and does not need any nerfs.


> {{champion:119}} 
> {{champion:67}} 
> {{champion:18}} 
> {{champion:81}} 
> {{champion:22}} 
> {{champion:236}} 
> Are fine, mostly, little tweaks here and there, but their problem is mostly a case of being outclassed by the quad.

I agree that these are fine.  I expect Vayne will become top tier as health stacking tanks become more common.  Ashe could maybe use some utility buffs to make sure that she stays as *THE* utility ADC (Kalista feels like she is currently infringing on that turf).  I am a fan of Ashe support though, so I may be biased in that regard.

> {{champion:96}} 
> {{champion:6}} (Fills in a Bruiser role, but his ADC needs buffing)
> {{champion:110}} 
> {{champion:29}} (Dear god twitch, poor Twitch, a shadow of your former self.)
> {{champion:133}} (Fills In a Bruiser role, but her ADC needs buffing)
> {{champion:21}} (Yes, I feel she needs some buffs here and there, but less so than the others.)
> Need buffs, some more than others.

Maybe some of these could be slightly buffed.  
I think Riot should closely watch {{champion:96}} Kog'Maw and {{champion:110}} Varus.  Those two should be doing well in a tank meta so if they don't start to rise in popularity, it should be taken as a sign that they may be undertuned.  
{{champion:29}} Twitch just needs some nerfs reversed...  I felt like he was balanced before his last round of nerfs...
{{champion:133}} I heard that Riot is making fixing Quinn's many bugs a priority.  Hopefully, that should help put her in a good spot.  Balancing her is tricky though since she can be a really dominant top-laner; the same goes for {{champion:6}} Urgot.  I'm not sure those two can/should be safely balanced around their performance as bot lane marksmen.
